    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "\\(\\dfrac{2\\tan x}{1+2\\tan^2x}=\\dfrac{2\\sin x\\cos x}{\\cos^2x+2\\sin^2x}=\\dfrac{\\sin2x}{1+\\sin^2x}\\)\n\nLet \\(t=1+\\sin^2x\\implies dt=\\sin2x\\,dx\\):\n\n\\(\\int\\dfrac{dt}{t}=\\log|1+\\sin^2x|+c=\\log\\left(\\dfrac{\\cos^2x}{2}+\\sin^2x\\right)+c\\)",
    "name": "Substitution Integral"
  },
  {
