    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "\\(\\dfrac{2+\\sin x}{1+\\cos x}=\\dfrac{2(1+\\tan^2(x/2))+2\\tan(x/2)}{2}=\\sec^2\\dfrac{x}{2}+\\tan\\dfrac{x}{2}\\)\n\nLet \\(t=x/2\\): \\(\\int e^t(\\sec^2t+\\tan t)\\cdot2\\,dt\\)\n\nUsing \\(\\int e^t(f(t)+f'(t))dt\\) with \\(f(t)=\\tan t\\):\n\n\\(=2e^t\\tan t+c=2e^{x/2}\\tan\\dfrac{x}{2}+c\\)",
